In this article, President Joe Biden discusses the significance of Father's Day and expresses his gratitude for the fathers and father figures who shape our lives. He reflects on his own father's teachings and how they influenced his parenting. He also acknowledges those who have lost fathers or children, recognizing the pain but finding solace in the enduring presence of loved ones. President Biden emphasizes his administration's commitment to supporting fathers and families, including funding for child care, paid leave, and creating safer communities. He concludes by proclaiming June 19, 2022, as Father's Day and urging everyone to honor and appreciate fathers and father figures.